SIMPLE: airiness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Airiness
<hw>Air"i*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state or quality
of being airy; openness or exposure to the air; <as>as, the
<ex>airiness</ex> of a country seat</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Lightness of spirits; gayety; levity; <as>as, the
<ex>airiness</ex> of young persons</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Airing</ent>⟦br⟧
